Session 5 is a classic CCEE favorite because it mixes concepts + architecture + real deployments (UTM, Reverse Proxy, Load Balancing, Server Farming).
Below are 30 CDAC-aligned MCQs (10 Basic + 10 Intermediate + 10 Advanced) mapped to Session 5 theory + Lab 8.

Network Defense & Countermeasures ‚Äì Session 5
BASIC MCQs (1‚Äì10)
1. ClearOS and pfSense are best classified as:
A. Hardware firewalls
B. Linux-based software firewalls
C. IDS systems
D. Antivirus platforms

2. A software firewall primarily runs on:
A. Network switch
B. Dedicated ASIC
C. General-purpose operating system
D. Router firmware only

3. A reverse proxy primarily sits:
A. Behind the client
B. Between client and server
C. Inside LAN only
D. After database

4. Which software is commonly used as a reverse proxy?
A. Apache
B. Nginx
C. Squid
D. Both B and C

5. A reverse proxy hides:
A. Client IP
B. Internal server details
C. Network bandwidth
D. DNS server

6. UTM stands for:
A. Unified Traffic Management
B. Universal Threat Monitor
C. Unified Threat Management
D. User Traffic Module

7. Which feature is typically part of a UTM device?
A. Load balancing only
B. IDS/IPS, Firewall, Antivirus
C. Proxy server only
D. Routing only

8. Server Load Balancing helps to:
A. Increase disk space
B. Distribute traffic across servers
C. Encrypt traffic
D. Replace firewall

9. Server farming refers to:
A. Database clustering
B. Multiple servers acting as one service
C. Single powerful server
D. Backup strategy

10. Which layer load balancing does Nginx commonly support?
A. Layer 2 only
B. Layer 3 only
C. Layer 4 & Layer 7
D. Layer 1

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11‚Äì20)
11. pfSense differs from traditional iptables mainly because it:
A. Uses Windows kernel
B. Provides GUI-based firewall management
C. Cannot do NAT
D. Is cloud-only

12. Reverse proxy improves security by:
A. Blocking all traffic
B. Exposing internal servers
C. Acting as an intermediary
D. Disabling direct connections

13. Squid is traditionally used as:
A. Packet filter
B. Forward proxy
C. Reverse proxy
D. IDS

14. In reverse proxy configuration, URL regex is mainly used to:
A. Encrypt URLs
B. Match and route requests
C. Block DNS
D. Improve bandwidth

15. Which load-balancing algorithm distributes requests sequentially?
A. Least connections
B. Hash-based
C. Round Robin
D. Random

16. UTM devices reduce complexity because they:
A. Replace all security tools
B. Integrate multiple security functions
C. Increase manual configuration
D. Eliminate risks

17. Server farming primarily improves:
A. Confidentiality
B. Availability and scalability
C. Integrity
D. Authentication

18. Which failure does load balancing directly mitigate?
A. Data breach
B. Single point of failure
C. Malware infection
D. Password cracking

19. Reverse proxy caching mainly helps to:
A. Improve performance
B. Encrypt traffic
C. Block attacks
D. Replace IDS

20. ClearOS is best suited for:
A. Endpoint security
B. Enterprise gateway security
C. Packet sniffing
D. Vulnerability scanning

ADVANCED MCQs (21‚Äì30)
21. From a security perspective, reverse proxy helps mitigate:
A. SQL injection
B. Direct server exposure
C. Insider attacks
D. Password reuse

22. Nginx load balancing at Layer 7 allows decisions based on:
A. MAC address
B. IP address only
C. HTTP headers and URLs
D. Physical interface

23. In a UTM deployment, which drawback is MOST significant?
A. Lack of GUI
B. Single point of failure
C. No firewall support
D. No IDS

24. Regex-based routing in reverse proxy is MOST useful when:
A. Serving static files
B. Hosting multiple applications on same domain
C. Encrypting sessions
D. Blocking IPs

25. Server farming combined with load balancing mainly addresses:
A. Confidentiality risks
B. Performance bottlenecks
C. User authentication
D. Malware detection

26. Squid used as reverse proxy differs from Nginx mainly in:
A. Kernel dependency
B. Caching capabilities
C. Port filtering
D. NAT support

27. Which deployment BEST improves both security and scalability?
A. Single server with firewall
B. Reverse proxy + server farm
C. UTM only
D. IDS only

28. If reverse proxy fails, the MOST immediate impact is:
A. Data corruption
B. Service unavailability
C. Loss of integrity
D. Malware spread

29. From CDAC CCEE perspective, UTM should be viewed as:
A. Replacement for all security layers
B. Part of defense-in-depth
C. Obsolete technology
D. Network performance tool

30. Which statement BEST aligns with CDAC exam philosophy?
A. Load balancers replace firewalls
B. Reverse proxy increases attack surface
C. Security and availability must coexist
D. UTM eliminates risk

ANSWER KEY
Basic:
1-B, 2-C, 3-B, 4-D, 5-B, 6-C, 7-B, 8-B, 9-B, 10-C

Intermediate:
11-B, 12-C, 13-B, 14-B, 15-C, 16-B, 17-B, 18-B, 19-A, 20-B

Advanced:
21-B, 22-C, 23-B, 24-B, 25-B, 26-B, 27-B, 28-B, 29-B, 30-C

